title: Pa. boys and girls: Harriton's Gillespie-Sickman wins Central League XC title
text:
Strath Haven won the team title with 38 points. Girls' Tennis Maddie Wood and Ashley Griffith of Conestoga won the Central League doubles tournament when their opponents, Amy Zhang and Julia Herman, also of Conestoga, had to retire because of injury after the first set.
Wood, a sophomore, and Griffith, a freshman, took the first set, 5-2, at Healthplex Sports Club. 
Pioneer Athletic Doubles Tournament. Jasmine Morris and Allison Newman of host Perkiomen Valley defeated Camryn Gelting and Delaney Kent of Owen J. Roberts, 6-3, 6-3, to win the title. Girls' Soccer Freshman Natalie Sgro scored five times to set the Baldwin single-game scoring record in a 6-3 Inter-Ac League win at Springside Chestnut Hill. 
Nonleague. Emma Loving had a hat trick and host Central Bucks East shut out West Chester Henderson, 3-0.
